# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: MagePath | Scene: MagePath3
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah woke to the sound of the door on her bedroom being thrown wide open."
    new "Sarah woke to the sound of the door on her bedroom being thrown wide open."

    old "No sooner had it done so, than that Xan stormed in."
    new "No sooner had it done so, than that Xan stormed in."

    old "Great news, Sarah, great news!"
    new "Great news, Sarah, great news!"

    old "Sarah wildly grabbed for the sheets, pulling them up to her chest."
    new "Sarah wildly grabbed for the sheets, pulling them up to her chest."

    old "Xan!"
    new "Xan!"

    old "I'm...I'm not decent!"
    new "I'm...I'm not decent!"

    old "She saw Xan turn red as he franctically spun himself around, facing away from the bed."
    new "She saw Xan turn red as he franctically spun himself around, facing away from the bed."

    old "I'm so sorry, I didn't know, I didn't think."
    new "I'm so sorry, I didn't know, I didn't think."

    old "Sorry, I just, I haven't lived with anyone else for so long, I fear I might have desocialized a bit."
    new "Sorry, I just, I haven't lived with anyone else for so long, I fear I might have desocialized a bit."

    old "Sarah quickly got dressed as Xan kept his back to her."
    new "Sarah quickly got dressed as Xan kept his back to her."

    old "Alright, I'm dressed, what were you saying?"
    new "Alright, I'm dressed, what were you saying?"

    old "Xan turned back around to face her."
    new "Xan turned back around to face her."

    old "A week ago, I contacted my mage order for a certain relic, and it's finally arrived!"
    new "A week ago, I contacted my mage order for a certain relic, and it's finally arrived!"

    old "Xan was holding out a sharp, rectangular pendant."
    new "Xan was holding out a sharp, rectangular pendant."

    old "It's...a necklace?"
    new "It's...a necklace?"

    old "She saw a shocked expression come across Xan's face."
    new "She saw a shocked expression come across Xan's face."

    old "It's a lot more than that, Sarah."
    new "It's a lot more than that, Sarah."

    old "This is the very thing that might change your life."
    new "This is the very thing that might change your life."

    old "My life?"
    new "My life?"

    old "You see, Sarah, I didn't want to say anything until I could be sure, but when I first met you, I didn't just invite you because I was being kind to you."
    new "You see, Sarah, I didn't want to say anything until I could be sure, but when I first met you, I didn't just invite you because I was being kind to you."

    old "I mean, that was part of it, but I saw something in you. A certain glimmer, it's hard to explain."
    new "I mean, that was part of it, but I saw something in you. A certain glimmer, it's hard to explain."

    old "It's often an indicator of magical potential."
    new "It's often an indicator of magical potential."

    old "Sarah found it all hard to process, especially early in the morning."
    new "Sarah found it all hard to process, especially early in the morning."

    old "Magical...potential?"
    new "Magical...potential?"

    old "Yes, Sarah! If I'm correct, this pendant will reveal your latent potential for magic."
    new "Yes, Sarah! If I'm correct, this pendant will reveal your latent potential for magic."

    old "You know what that means?"
    new "You know what that means?"

    old "Sarah looked Xan in the eyes, she shook her head."
    new "Sarah looked Xan in the eyes, she shook her head."

    old "I could take you and as my apprentice! I could teach you how to tap into your magical abilities."
    new "I could take you and as my apprentice! I could teach you how to tap into your magical abilities."

    old "Sarah had imagined a lot of things for her life, but never that."
    new "Sarah had imagined a lot of things for her life, but never that."

    old "You mean...I could learn to wield magic?"
    new "You mean...I could learn to wield magic?"

    old "The potential is endless, Sarah. You can learn to fly, shake the earth, create items out of thin air."
    new "The potential is endless, Sarah. You can learn to fly, shake the earth, create items out of thin air."

    old "Do you remember how scared you were, back in the alley?"
    new "Do you remember how scared you were, back in the alley?"

    old "Sarah did remember, though she didn't want to."
    new "Sarah did remember, though she didn't want to."

    old "If you learned magic, you could turn a lowlife like that into ashes with the snap of a finger."
    new "If you learned magic, you could turn a lowlife like that into ashes with the snap of a finger."

    old "That was an idea that did seem to appeal to her."
    new "That was an idea that did seem to appeal to her."

    old "Xan stepped across the room and grabbed her by the shoulders."
    new "Xan stepped across the room and grabbed her by the shoulders."

    old "Don't you see, Sarah? You thought you had no path in life left, and you just randomly end up on my doorstep, as a magical potentiate?"
    new "Don't you see, Sarah? You thought you had no path in life left, and you just randomly end up on my doorstep, as a magical potentiate?"

    old "That's not luck, that's fate. Fate brought you right to my doorstep."
    new "That's not luck, that's fate. Fate brought you right to my doorstep."

    old "Sarah broke free from Xan's grip."
    new "Sarah broke free from Xan's grip."

    old "But we don't know anything...maybe I don't have any magical abilities."
    new "But we don't know anything...maybe I don't have any magical abilities."

    old "Hold out your hand."
    new "Hold out your hand."

    old "Reluctantly, Sarah did as told."
    new "Reluctantly, Sarah did as told."

    old "Xan raised the relic above her hands and dropped it into the palm of her hands."
    new "Xan raised the relic above her hands and dropped it into the palm of her hands."

    old "The moment it made contact with her skin, a bright light began to shine forth from the object."
    new "The moment it made contact with her skin, a bright light began to shine forth from the object."

    old "Sarah knew little of magic, or the relic, but even she could conclude that it confirmed Xan's suspicion."
    new "Sarah knew little of magic, or the relic, but even she could conclude that it confirmed Xan's suspicion."

    old "Amazing! I knew it!"
    new "Amazing! I knew it!"

    old "What did I tell you, Sarah? Fate!"
    new "What did I tell you, Sarah? Fate!"

    old "Sarah began to think."
    new "Sarah began to think."

    old "She had arrived here. She had nothing left to her name. No direction to move towards."
    new "She had arrived here. She had nothing left to her name. No direction to move towards."

    old "And now, she had a purpose thrust onto her."
    new "And now, she had a purpose thrust onto her."

    old "A path that she could follow, but perhaps above all, something tha could make her powerful. She'd never have to be scared again."
    new "A path that she could follow, but perhaps above all, something tha could make her powerful. She'd never have to be scared again."

    old "She wanted this."
    new "She wanted this."

    old "So much was coming at her, so fast, and yet she knew that much. She knew that she wanted this. The power of it."
    new "So much was coming at her, so fast, and yet she knew that much. She knew that she wanted this. The power of it."

    old "She turned to face Xan."
    new "She turned to face Xan."

    old "Will you teach me?"
    new "Will you teach me?"

    old "Xan's smile was beaming. She'd never seen him this happy before."
    new "Xan's smile was beaming. She'd never seen him this happy before."

    old "Of course Sarah! I'll teach you everything there is to know about magic, and trust me, you won't find a better teacher than me."
    new "Of course Sarah! I'll teach you everything there is to know about magic, and trust me, you won't find a better teacher than me."

    old "Well, not out in the world any way, there are some in the citadel, perhaps, but you'll meet them in time too!"
    new "Well, not out in the world any way, there are some in the citadel, perhaps, but you'll meet them in time too!"

    old "Xan was running around the room in a frenzy."
    new "Xan was running around the room in a frenzy."

    old "I can't wait for you to begin learning all of this!"
    new "I can't wait for you to begin learning all of this!"

    old "You're going to need master Kairan's guide to inital leyline readings..."
    new "You're going to need master Kairan's guide to inital leyline readings..."

    old "Ooh, and can't forget master Baal's introduction to western normative spellweaving..."
    new "Ooh, and can't forget master Baal's introduction to western normative spellweaving..."

    old "Sarah watched, detached, as Xan began to pull books off shelves and out of chests that she had barely realized were there."
    new "Sarah watched, detached, as Xan began to pull books off shelves and out of chests that she had barely realized were there."

    old "One stack after the other was pushed into her arms."
    new "One stack after the other was pushed into her arms."

    old "Struggling to hold onto them, Sarah began to throw some onto the bed, but soon as she did Xan would add more to the pile."
    new "Struggling to hold onto them, Sarah began to throw some onto the bed, but soon as she did Xan would add more to the pile."

    old "Sarah dropped the entire pile of books from her hand, onto the bed."
    new "Sarah dropped the entire pile of books from her hand, onto the bed."

    old "Xan..."
    new "Xan..."

    old "Xan continued collecting more books."
    new "Xan continued collecting more books."

    old "Raising her voice, she found his attention."
    new "Raising her voice, she found his attention."

    old "This...it's a lot for me..."
    new "This...it's a lot for me..."

    old "You storm in here, you tell me I have magic powers...now you're handing me more books than I know what to do with..."
    new "You storm in here, you tell me I have magic powers...now you're handing me more books than I know what to do with..."

    old "If you want me to become a mage, you're going to have to let me process this first."
    new "If you want me to become a mage, you're going to have to let me process this first."

    old "Xan suddenly looked embarrassed for his enthusiasm."
    new "Xan suddenly looked embarrassed for his enthusiasm."

    old "I've been living alone for quite some time. It's been many years more since I last took an apprentice."
    new "I've been living alone for quite some time. It's been many years more since I last took an apprentice."

    old "The idea just got me so excited, but that isn't fair to you."
    new "The idea just got me so excited, but that isn't fair to you."

    old "I should have given you time to process what this all means."
    new "I should have given you time to process what this all means."

    old "Xan opened the door and stepped out."
    new "Xan opened the door and stepped out."

    old "I'll be in the study when you're ready."
    new "I'll be in the study when you're ready."

    old "Take this and try it on, maybe it will help it all feel real."
    new "Take this and try it on, maybe it will help it all feel real."

    old "He put down a package and closed the door. Sarah heard him leave."
    new "He put down a package and closed the door. Sarah heard him leave."

    old "Sarah walked over towards the package and grabbed it off the floor. She pulled on the velvet strings and as they slipped away, they revealed an outfit."
    new "Sarah walked over towards the package and grabbed it off the floor. She pulled on the velvet strings and as they slipped away, they revealed an outfit."

    old "Why not try it, she wondered."
    new "Why not try it, she wondered."

    old "Sarah got undressed."
    new "Sarah got undressed."

    old "Struggling for a moment with the clothes, Sarah wondered if they had even been made to suit a woman."
    new "Struggling for a moment with the clothes, Sarah wondered if they had even been made to suit a woman."

    old "Finally, after some attempts, she managed to get them on."
    new "Finally, after some attempts, she managed to get them on."

    old "Sarah walked up towards the only mirror in the room and stood in front of it."
    new "Sarah walked up towards the only mirror in the room and stood in front of it."

    old "It wasn't much compared to what she had in Castle Reinmeer, but it was enough."
    new "It wasn't much compared to what she had in Castle Reinmeer, but it was enough."

    old "The cloth pressed against her skin, and to her surprise felt soft as silk."
    new "The cloth pressed against her skin, and to her surprise felt soft as silk."

    old "Much about the clothes began to surprise Sarah."
    new "Much about the clothes began to surprise Sarah."

    old "The weight she expected was absent, and her every step seemed somehow soft and muted."
    new "The weight she expected was absent, and her every step seemed somehow soft and muted."

    old "Sarah suspected the clothes themselves had magical properties."
    new "Sarah suspected the clothes themselves had magical properties."

    old "Who was to say, she concluded, she knew so little of this new world she was stepping into."
    new "Who was to say, she concluded, she knew so little of this new world she was stepping into."

    old "But she knew that she had to."
    new "But she knew that she had to."

    old "Everything else had been taken from her. She had been left to fend for herself, and she had almost died on her first night out on the street."
    new "Everything else had been taken from her. She had been left to fend for herself, and she had almost died on her first night out on the street."

    old "Here, in this house, she felt safe."
    new "Here, in this house, she felt safe."

    old "More importantly, she had felt as if she had a purpose, and now, she could feel that purpose growing."
    new "More importantly, she had felt as if she had a purpose, and now, she could feel that purpose growing."

    old "Magic."
    new "Magic."

    old "If nothing else, it would prove a powerful weapon in her hands."
    new "If nothing else, it would prove a powerful weapon in her hands."

    old "Sarah steeled herself and looked into the mirror, meeting her own eyes."
    new "Sarah steeled herself and looked into the mirror, meeting her own eyes."

    old "She would walk this path."
    new "She would walk this path."

    old "Sarah turned to the door and left for the study."
    new "Sarah turned to the door and left for the study."

    old "Sarah walked into the study, leaving her doubts behind her."
    new "Sarah walked into the study, leaving her doubts behind her."

    old "Xan."
    new "Xan."

    old "Xan looked up at her. She suspected there was a hint of worry in his eyes."
    new "Xan looked up at her. She suspected there was a hint of worry in his eyes."

    old "I've made up my mind. I'll become your apprentice."
    new "I've made up my mind. I'll become your apprentice."

    old "Xan stood up and embraced Sarah."
    new "Xan stood up and embraced Sarah."

    old "Sarah! That's amazing."
    new "Sarah! That's amazing."

    old "I'm so sorry for my earlier rush, I promise that I will try to be more considerate."
    new "I'm so sorry for my earlier rush, I promise that I will try to be more considerate."

    old "Xan looked confused."
    new "Xan looked confused."

    old "I'll become your apprentice, but I don't want you to go easy on me."
    new "I'll become your apprentice, but I don't want you to go easy on me."

    old "Everything about this life...it's strange and new to me. If I go down this path, I want to go as fast as possible."
    new "Everything about this life...it's strange and new to me. If I go down this path, I want to go as fast as possible."

    old "I'll teach you Sarah. And I promise I'll go so fast your head is going to spin, but you need to understand, this isn't easy."
    new "I'll teach you Sarah. And I promise I'll go so fast your head is going to spin, but you need to understand, this isn't easy."

    old "There are those who have the potential, but who never master the basics."
    new "There are those who have the potential, but who never master the basics."

    old "Learning to master magic is a lifetime of effort, and it might be years before you're even mildly able to wield it."
    new "Learning to master magic is a lifetime of effort, and it might be years before you're even mildly able to wield it."

    old "Don't expect that you'll master the oldest art in a few months."
    new "Don't expect that you'll master the oldest art in a few months."

    old "I understand, Xan. Just promise me that you'll go fast."
    new "I understand, Xan. Just promise me that you'll go fast."

    old "And the mage kept his word."
    new "And the mage kept his word."

    old "For the remainder of the day, Xan began to teach Sarah the introductions to magic."
    new "For the remainder of the day, Xan began to teach Sarah the introductions to magic."

    old "He performed small spells, showing her the possibilities. Destructive, creative, and utterly otherworldly."
    new "He performed small spells, showing her the possibilities. Destructive, creative, and utterly otherworldly."

    old "Light danced around his body, twitching to his every command. It was a pure light, yet unlike the sun, it never stung her eyes."
    new "Light danced around his body, twitching to his every command. It was a pure light, yet unlike the sun, it never stung her eyes."

    old "Magic is in it's first stage essential."
    new "Magic is in it's first stage essential."

    old "There are those who simply can wield, and those who simply never can wield it."
    new "There are those who simply can wield, and those who simply never can wield it."

    old "There are theories, but the truth is, we don't know how or what determines a person's apptitude for magic."
    new "There are theories, but the truth is, we don't know how or what determines a person's apptitude for magic."

    old "Once the potential is present, a person can be trained to wield magic, but without training even those with potential will never be able to learn it."
    new "Once the potential is present, a person can be trained to wield magic, but without training even those with potential will never be able to learn it."

    old "Sarah nodded and intently listened to his every word. With each new lecture, new worlds began to open to her."
    new "Sarah nodded and intently listened to his every word. With each new lecture, new worlds began to open to her."

    old "The first part of your training will simply involve becoming aware of your own magic. Learning to feel and move it, like becoming aware of a limb or a muscle you never knew you had."
    new "The first part of your training will simply involve becoming aware of your own magic. Learning to feel and move it, like becoming aware of a limb or a muscle you never knew you had."

    old "After that, we will move onto learning how you can manipulate and fold this energy into practical spells."
    new "After that, we will move onto learning how you can manipulate and fold this energy into practical spells."

    old "On and on went Xan."
    new "On and on went Xan."

    old "And yet, Sarah never tired. She hang on his every word."
    new "And yet, Sarah never tired. She hang on his every word."

    old "Before she had well and truly realized it, night had set in, and even the inexhaustible Xan seemed near to sleep."
    new "Before she had well and truly realized it, night had set in, and even the inexhaustible Xan seemed near to sleep."

    old "We'll continue this further tomorrow. It's been a long time since I've had to talk so much, you'll have to excuse me."
    new "We'll continue this further tomorrow. It's been a long time since I've had to talk so much, you'll have to excuse me."

    old "Sarah patted Xan on the shoulder."
    new "Sarah patted Xan on the shoulder."

    old "Don't be sorry, it was a lot for both of us."
    new "Don't be sorry, it was a lot for both of us."

    old "Xan gratefully nodded and left towards his room to sleep."
    new "Xan gratefully nodded and left towards his room to sleep."

    old "Sarah took in the room, now all alone. It's many tomes, trinkets and relics."
    new "Sarah took in the room, now all alone. It's many tomes, trinkets and relics."

    old "It all began to feel familiar to her, as if this could be more than a place to be safe, but a home."
    new "It all began to feel familiar to her, as if this could be more than a place to be safe, but a home."

    old "But a thought creeped into Sarah's mind."
    new "But a thought creeped into Sarah's mind."

    old "The words of the spirit Razaphel penetrated her calm mood."
    new "The words of the spirit Razaphel penetrated her calm mood."

    old "Secrets...deceit..."
    new "Secrets...deceit..."

    old "Not all was as it appeared, or at least, so the spirit claimed."
    new "Not all was as it appeared, or at least, so the spirit claimed."

    old "She had chosen to believe him and given up her body in return for information. She wanted to make good on that bargain."
    new "She had chosen to believe him and given up her body in return for information. She wanted to make good on that bargain."

    old "Slipping out onto the hallway, Sarah made her way towards the room of the spirit, making certain not to wake anyone."
    new "Slipping out onto the hallway, Sarah made her way towards the room of the spirit, making certain not to wake anyone."

    old "As always, the room was silent. It was an ominous silence, the kind of silence that one could hear in a forest full of predators."
    new "As always, the room was silent. It was an ominous silence, the kind of silence that one could hear in a forest full of predators."

    old "Sarah chose to break it."
    new "Sarah chose to break it."

    old "A moment of pause."
    new "A moment of pause."

    old "Razaphel, show yourself..."
    new "Razaphel, show yourself..."

    old "Upon this command, Sarah could see the smoke began to swirl, revealing the spirit's uncertain form."
    new "Upon this command, Sarah could see the smoke began to swirl, revealing the spirit's uncertain form."

    old "You return."
    new "You return."

    old "Come to offer up more of yourself?"
    new "Come to offer up more of yourself?"

    old "I've come to collect on what is due to me."
    new "I've come to collect on what is due to me."

    old "A laugh that sounded like a hiss, eminated from the creature."
    new "A laugh that sounded like a hiss, eminated from the creature."

    old "He's got his claws into you."
    new "He's got his claws into you."

    old "Has you dressed up like a little apprentice."
    new "Has you dressed up like a little apprentice."

    old "Turns out I have magical potential."
    new "Turns out I have magical potential."

    old "Ooh, that much I knew."
    new "Ooh, that much I knew."

    old "The spirit's body swirled, more energized."
    new "The spirit's body swirled, more energized."

    old "This world appears to me very different than it does to you."
    new "This world appears to me very different than it does to you."

    old "There are things I can see, and things I cannot see. This limits me in some ways, but frees me up in others."
    new "There are things I can see, and things I cannot see. This limits me in some ways, but frees me up in others."

    old "Your...potential...I can see it around you."
    new "Your...potential...I can see it around you."

    old "Sarah observed the spirit."
    new "Sarah observed the spirit."

    old "What does it look like?"
    new "What does it look like?"

    old "Like a crown, made out of starlight, balanced atop your head."
    new "Like a crown, made out of starlight, balanced atop your head."

    old "Sarah tried to make sense of his words. They seemed too odd to be meant to deceive."
    new "Sarah tried to make sense of his words. They seemed too odd to be meant to deceive."

    old "Does it mean anything?"
    new "Does it mean anything?"

    old "Please...don't force me to speak on it much more. It pains me to look at it."
    new "Please...don't force me to speak on it much more. It pains me to look at it."

    old "It pains you to look at me?"
    new "It pains you to look at me?"

    old "Only when I focus on it too much, and sometimes it can dim, the starlight."
    new "Only when I focus on it too much, and sometimes it can dim, the starlight."

    old "Dim?"
    new "Dim?"

    old "Yes. When last we played."
    new "Yes. When last we played."

    old "Sarah felt the memories flood back to her, being pinned down, her every orifice ravaged by this creature. Pleasure, nearing madness."
    new "Sarah felt the memories flood back to her, being pinned down, her every orifice ravaged by this creature. Pleasure, nearing madness."

    old "That's right. You remember that I gave you something, and you promised me something in return?"
    new "That's right. You remember that I gave you something, and you promised me something in return?"

    old "The spirit flowed through the air for a moment before speaking."
    new "The spirit flowed through the air for a moment before speaking."

    old "You make it all sound so transactional, Sarah. You mean to tell me it was all for me?"
    new "You make it all sound so transactional, Sarah. You mean to tell me it was all for me?"

    old "I liked it"
    new "I liked it"

    old "Sarah looked directly at the spirit."
    new "Sarah looked directly at the spirit."

    old "I won't deny that I liked it."
    new "I won't deny that I liked it."

    old "Another laugh sounding like a hiss."
    new "Another laugh sounding like a hiss."

    old "Good. It would have been pointless to deny it. When you're near me, your feelings are as visible to me as your physical form."
    new "Good. It would have been pointless to deny it. When you're near me, your feelings are as visible to me as your physical form."

    old "So many of you humans try to hide this desire...but not you..."
    new "So many of you humans try to hide this desire...but not you..."

    old "And what of you, spirit?"
    new "And what of you, spirit?"

    old "My pleasure is of a different kind...but I won't deny that I felt sated."
    new "My pleasure is of a different kind...but I won't deny that I felt sated."

    old "I only did it for the information"
    new "I only did it for the information"

    old "Sarah tried to face down the spirit."
    new "Sarah tried to face down the spirit."

    old "I only did it for the information."
    new "I only did it for the information."

    old "If you say so..."
    new "If you say so..."

    old "Sarah hoped the spirit believed her. She wondered if she herself did."
    new "Sarah hoped the spirit believed her. She wondered if she herself did."

    old "Regardless...you owe me what was promised. Information."
    new "Regardless...you owe me what was promised. Information."

    old "Aah...yes...I did offer something in return, didn't I? What was it."
    new "Aah...yes...I did offer something in return, didn't I? What was it."

    old "You said Xan lied to me. That he would deceive me."
    new "You said Xan lied to me. That he would deceive me."

    old "That was it. That abominable mage..."
    new "That was it. That abominable mage..."

    old "For a moment, Razaphel hung in the air, slowly drifting, considering."
    new "For a moment, Razaphel hung in the air, slowly drifting, considering."

    old "He plays his part well. The inattentive fool, the distant intellectual..."
    new "He plays his part well. The inattentive fool, the distant intellectual..."

    old "But this is not who he is. His every performance is meant to deceive you."
    new "But this is not who he is. His every performance is meant to deceive you."

    old "Why would he do that? He's so many times more powerful than me, why would he have need to trick me."
    new "Why would he do that? He's so many times more powerful than me, why would he have need to trick me."

    old "Because for what he wants, force cannot work."
    new "Because for what he wants, force cannot work."

    old "You are like a blade to him, unrivaled in potential quality. A weapon that he can wield towards his own ends. A tool, or an instrument."
    new "You are like a blade to him, unrivaled in potential quality. A weapon that he can wield towards his own ends. A tool, or an instrument."

    old "Sarah tried to understand."
    new "Sarah tried to understand."

    old "You mean my magic? I barely know anything. What can I do that he can't?"
    new "You mean my magic? I barely know anything. What can I do that he can't?"

    old "This is true for now, but he imagines you will grow powerful. And he is not wrong."
    new "This is true for now, but he imagines you will grow powerful. And he is not wrong."

    old "But more than just your power, he seeks to wield the source of your power. The starlight crown atop your head."
    new "But more than just your power, he seeks to wield the source of your power. The starlight crown atop your head."

